{{wikipedia}}

==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[Late Latin]] '''[[sarcasmus]]''', from [[Greek]] '''[[sarkasmos]]''', from '''[[sarkazein]]'''  "bite the lips in rage", from combining form '''[[sark-]]''', from '''[[sarx]]''', ''[[flesh]]''.

===Noun===

{{en-noun}}

# {{uncountable}} A form of [[humor]] that is marked by [[mock]]ing with [[irony]], typically with [[vocal]] over-[[emphasis]] via [[tone]] or [[volume]] ([[cf.]], [[farce]])
# {{countable}} Act of sarcasm.

